    public interface BuckEventExternalInterface
    Describes a generic buck event. This type is intended to be used by external applications (like the Intellij Buck plugin) to deserialize events coming from the webserver.

      • storeLastInstanceAndReplayForNewClients

        default boolean storeLastInstanceAndReplayForNewClients()
        By default, events sent to external websocket listeners are fire-and-forget; a client never receives past events. However events may opt in to a behavior where the last instance of the event is stored and sent to new clients as they connect. This is useful for "snapshot" events which provide information about an ongoing event.

        Note that this does not replay multiple instances of an event. Only the last instance will be sent to new clients.
